    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Adding an Exception to Norton Firewall</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">By following below mentioned steps, you can add an exception to the Norton Firewall:</para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Open the main page of Norton Internet Security.</li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">Left-click on Settings in the upper right hand corner of the Network window.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">Under Firewall &gt; Program Control left-click on Configure</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">Select Add.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">Browse the list starting from My Computer to the Licensing folder. The path for this program is C:\ProgramData\CivilGeo\Licensing</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">Select â€œLicense ServiceApp.exeâ€ and press Open.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text">Make sure to select Allow and then OK on the security request.</text></li>
    </list>
